Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with three-quarter Helios head as symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 175, 11? Name Xenophanes?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0861)
